HEADWORD: Englue
<hw>En*glue"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>en-</ets> + <ets>glue</ets>: cf. F. <ets>engluer</ets> to smear
with birdlime.]</ety> <def>To join or close fast together, as with glue;
<as>as, a coffer well <ex>englued</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

